column14: Comments
Thanks for the great way to give kids books.
Everything is too slow delayed it’s terrible
Customer service very helpful with my questions.
easy navigation throughout the site
The site kept freezing up  and I had to restart several times.
Had to submit a parent order and had time to browse.
I was hard to pick the books I wanted for bonus points/money.  I had to keep exiting the bonus order and got frustrated.

When I am in the shopping cart, it shows me the student orders. Then when I am on the last page putting in extra codes, free books, etc., it asks how many students placed orders and I have to go back out of the cart to double-check. It is a little thing, but could the number of student orders show up on the last page as well?
Just started looking - did not have time yet to place an order!
Trying to find parent letter to remind them that orders are due,
There are certain books missing, please provide more box sets for different series.
One of the books my parents ordered is out of stock.  Additionally, one of the books I had in my order for my classroom was out of stock as well.

I wish the YA books gave a slight description underneath them vs having to click into them to see what they're about. As a parent of 2 teens and a little one I could more easily shop for the big kids if the descriptions were on there.
N/A
I wasn't able to get a quick glance at the order at submitted
some of the books i could not fine
Wish the prices were a bit lower
I used to get to order books from this company when I was a kid, so its a joy to see that its still around 40 years later!
We love scholastic.
I miss the variety of $5 book offers to use with my classroom coupons like you offered in past years.
NA
The site and ordering process is very easy. Thank you!
Can't find how to load e wallet. I am only seeing a option to purchase gift card which is not what i want
More bilingual books (or books only in Spanish) please! Thank you for an easy purchasing experience!
always easy to navigate.

There was a lot of issues with my clicking to close a book's details, and inadvertently also opening whatever item was lying underneath the opened modal.  The behavior was that of almost double-clicking. As a work-around after several occurrences of this behavior, I resorted to using the "esc" button to close the book details modal.  There was also some delayed responses to the site as I navigated through it.  This may have been the result of my working from my parents' rural farm, as opposed to from my home. (Keziah Renee and I are on her spring break and so are traveling.)
I love everything on the site.  I have been a bit confused by the invoices that were sent in February.  Lots of teachers were in a panic.
I was unable to order the weekly $1 book with the bonus money I earned with my order.

My student's book has not been shipped yet.  Emma Sarian ordered "You Guac My World" in February and has not received her book yet.  It was initially out of stock, bit now it is back in stock and the book is still showing not shipped yet.  Please help.  My email is liana.tatoyan@lausd.net
Demasiado tiempo para acer la. Orden.

I tried logging in earlier and couldn’t get to the part to put in student orders . I tried logging in from one of my emails where a student ordered & was finally able to put in my students orders.   It shouldn’t be that complicated.
Great Experience!
Such a well designed website!!!
All good
There is balance left on my egift card, I'm not sure whether I can print voucher include the balance.  I'll try it next book fair.
Terrible website. Everything takes multiple clicks to find. Nothing formats correctly to anything other laptop.
Very good. Yes
Overall, it was easy to navigate and find other books that are not listed on paper book lists.
Very easy to use!
It won't go to the check out page
very helpful
Scholastic has the best customer service. Every time I call, I am extremely satisfied with the help.
My son is in 2 classes and I was trying to order for one class but the other kept coming up. I had to delete everything and start over for it to work.

All of the books that I purchase need to be leveled before putting them in my classroom library.  Very often I am not able to find a reading level (ex. P or Q) and have to go to other sites to find them.  I would love it if you had all books listed with a specific level.  For example, I purchased a Dragon  Girls 3 pack  and was unable to find the level for any of the books. It just states that the lot of books are leveled from N to O.  I need to know the individual book levels.
I shouldn't have to pay taxes and shipping on students books.
I am a grandparent of 2 children whose teachers are involved with Scholastic Book Club.  Selection of books is very good, and ordering is convenient and fast.

Scholastic has been MUCH better this year. Last year, I stopped using Scholastic in my classroom because of so many issues with shipping, money accounts, customer service issues, etc. This year has been like it was in the past before the pandemic! So glad the Scholastic I know is back!!!

I was really sad that the books I was looking for are not available. I wanted to buy a set for my son's teacher to keep in her classroom. I searched for Gregor the Overlander series and A Tale of Magic by Chris Colfer.  You carry The Hunger Games but not Gregor the Overlander, by the same author. I don't understand why.
Great book deals
hi hi hi hi hi
Very confusing website. I have always liked ordering Scholastic, but it is not intuitive working with the website.

It was difficult for me to find where my student placed an order. Perhaps a banner or alert button can come up for the teacher to access that quickly, rather than spending a lot of time trying to find where the student online order is.
The site is not very easy to navigate in order to add funds, get a gift card number or really do much
Every time I went to check on something I had to reenter my coupon number and choices.  I couldn't do a school Purchase order and leave off the tax for tax exempt.
Sometimes the search doesn't work when I am looking for specific books. I have to use a search engine like google for your book listings to show up. It can be frustrating.
My trust is still not back from my experience last year.

I found two different  teacher wish lists areas for the same teacher and they both contained different things.    Also, I did like that I could look at the monthly brochures online and click on each item within the brochure.  The fact that it wasn't just a photo and each item linked directly to the description and ordering information was so helpful.

I'm a retired elementary school teacher.  I'm here today supporting my grandchildren.  Thank you for offering popular/classic books at a lower price than I've seen at other places.  It's an important thing to do!
It was easy to order from the online flyer.  I prefer online ordering because I am able to order books that are not in the flyer that the teacher sent home to meet my daughter's reading level.
Waiting until tomorrow because the number of orders will increase.
Site has gotten better but it's still hard to navigate.  It's confusing to toggle between student site, teacher site, and teacher bonus point site
Difficulty: Could not zoom in on the top RH corner of the first page of the Club Leo flyer.
My order was not due today...just adding the one as it came in today.
I wish there were better ways to sort with a filter.
This was my first time placing an order. I was so happy to see I could enter my students' orders online!
I love the 5 for $5 books.
Kept knocking me out
Finding ANYTHING on your site is extremely difficult.  Without a flyer with an item number, I cannot find anything by name.  It should not be that difficult to place an order.
Kept freezing and closing my page which was frustrating
I cannot find the free book

I have been ordering from Scholastic Book Clubs for over 40 years.  I started ordering as a child then I started ordering as a teacher and parent.  I have always loved the great book selections and rewards that I have earned and/or ordered for my classroom and children.  Unfortunately, in the past few years I have been saddened by the topics/pictures that are in many of the books.  I am praying over whether I will continue to keep Scholastic as part of my classroom.  There is no guide in the small descriptions on the true content of the books/stories.  I have had to throw away a few books due to the content not matching my beliefs.
The lack of “step to reading”  was upsetting. I don’t feel all the groups are represented.

Can’t find how to get books to connect to teacher OR if they will get my order. Can’t find the same books I found over at the other site. Sorry Amazon is such a big competitor to yours I’m getting them cheaper there but was wanting to give credit to teacher(s).
some difficulties checking out

First tried ordering online using cell phone, but had much difficulty finding log in for the school code and ordering what came in the order form from school. Was much easier navigating on home computer.
Good one
Thank you for keeping it easy to order and quick to put look up info for scholars interested in buying but not having money yet.  This helps keep their interest.
tried to add books using points and it was showing a balance I owed
I use this site to help my students learn to love reading and start their own at home library! I LOVE IT!

Website is confusing to navigate and trying to order books with points is archaic. It is not a user friendly site. I do not get book orders that are age appropriate for 4/5 year olds. I only have been getting Early Childhood flyers which are in my opinion baby books. Firefly never comes. We prefer to send paper orders rather than constant emails to parents. Children like visuals.
For some reason I had trouble finding the flyer that was sent home last week on the website.  I did find what   I was looking for though.
I was looking to see what books were available as an option for an end of the year gift for my students.  There were some options but nothing caught my eye, so I will continue to look.

1. I like looking at the fliers with my children then ordering online    2. it  would be better if the recommendations more closely matched the books selected. I ordered some Nat Geo books and got recommendations for all kinds of random books. I wanted to see more nat geo.
Verifying security photos
TOO DIFFICUT TO GET FREE $5 BOOK
Book Felix is so cool

I didn't receive everything in my order.  I was contacting chat to find out how to get my replacements.  I was not able to get the agent to send me the replacements.  I had to send another email to get some help with the replacement stickers.
Flyers wouldn't open.
Very smooth and easy to order! I love receiving coupons for bonus points.
I wanted to use two payment methods..in other words, finish using up the funds on one card and pay the balance with our credit card, but was not able to do so.
I had bonus points to put in and it took me awhile to figure out how to do it.
We are grateful at how easy the Scholastic site is to use. Parents entering their orders online saves our staff so much time and the ease of processing those orders is amazing.

It is extremely difficult to determine whether a book is the appropriate grade level for a child on this site.  Most parents don't know the reading level codes, and having to look at so many different types is time consuming and annoying.  The grade level ranges are also so large that it's hard to asses whether a book will be too hard or easy for a child.  If you could just provide more images of the pages and table of contents (if applicable), that would help immensely.  I often look for these books online to figure out which is appropriate, but I might as well buy it at that place rather than Scholastic.
The format that confused me earlier in the year have not been changed.  It could still confuse anyone.
After entering the code, I couldn't add the free book to my order when I was using my phone because it wouldn't let me click the book to select it. I had to log into my computer to do so.

I am disappointed in the book selection.  Over the last few years, your book selection has gotten worse.  I have read Tuck Everlasting in my class for years, and I now have to go elsewhere to purchase them.
Website is glitchy through mobile, hard to checkout because certain buttons hidden etc.
Cannot locate E-wallet easily for book fair
Not needed today, but in the past, customer service was very helpful.

Things got crazy during covid, and some of my past orders weren't filled all-the-way... I guess shipping from printer to store was the issue. I'm hoping that's resolved. Did not order anything today because my kids are in bed, and I wanted to ask their opinions.
Wish I could get all the series for Eerie Elementary not just what was available:)
I would like to get into the $1.00 shopping without purchasing anything.  I order books for students who cannot afford them.

I miss having access to $1 books without having to spend $100.  My school is over 50% poverty and many students are not able to buy books. I am buying books out of my own pocket and I can't afford to spend $100 just to get to the $1 books.  I wish it would go back to how it was 4-5 years ago.  :(
Thank you!

I couldn't submit at first, finally saw I had to choose if school or home to send. Usually when you order something and miss a line, it pops up highlighted. I had to search to see what was missing.  Also i am unsure if teacher has sent in an order, so how do I know if my child will get the book?
I forgot my coupon on my desk, so I will submit my order first thing in the morning.
It's confusing to find things, but great books at great prices!
When I put in the item #, it did not work.

The page introduces the ewallet,  but it is hard to find how much money left on the card, and  don't know how to add more money to the card for the kid to use at school book fair.  The flow of finding thing is hard on the web page
Great site. Would really like to make sure more books were offered for older students.
Why are teachers being charged TAX??  I’m buying books for my classroom.  This isn’t okay.
It’s difficult to add items to your cart

The only thing about placing class book orders is when we unlock the $1 book store. I feel like the variety doesn't change, it's pretty much the same books. I like to purchase a book for each student in my class from this store when we order, but this month I wasn't able to because it was the same books that have been there.  Would just like to see this change each month.

The website kicks me out too soon after being inactive.  I am a teacher who usually gets started on an order and needs to complete it later on, and sometime I need more time.  I wish it wouldn’t kick me out so soon.  I just tried to say that I was still using the site, but it kicked me out anyways and had to log back in.
Wonderful experiance! I promised my grandaughter I would order the books but then missed the deadline at school. i was able to find the teacher on line and order with the class order. Yeah!!

I was not able to order Room to Dream as a stand-alone book.  It was only available as part of the Front Desk set.   (The other 3 books were available individually.)  This is irritating, because I have the other 3 books in my classroom library, and don't want to spend over $20 to get the one book I'm missing.

I really just wanted to log in and take care of funding my kids for the upcoming book fair. It is kind of frustrating that there isn't a link to the book fair stuff after you log into your class page.--like have a link somewhere obvious on the page back to the book fairs, etc. It would be more convenient if I could just log into my account and be able to easily access everything to do with Scholastic -- both ordering books and dealing with book fair. Also, both of my kids are listed on that book club page, and I would have preferred to have a way to set up the ewallet for them right there. I managed to do what I wanted, it just took longer than I expected because I had to open another tab with the main Scholastic page and search for our school's  book fair through that....and then had to go through the process twice to make two ewallets....would have liked to just set them up together. Maybe there's a way to do that, but it's not obvious. This site could be easier to navigate.
I appreciate how easy it was for me to navigate (even with my lack of experience shopping online).   Thank you for making it so automatic!
I’m hoping the order comes in before Easter break.🤞🏻
I was confused as to how to use the money I raised with a campaign, but I called in and the lady helped me very quickly!
I think the timeout time is too short.  I had a few short interruptions while entering my order, and it was a hassle to log back in each time. I was very glad the site saved my progress, though.
The reads free $5 book is confusing.  It’s hard to understand how to use it and to pick the free book.
Did not see apple rewards until after I submitted my order.

I'm trying to change my school for next year, but my new school is not on the zip code list. I tried to search by state and city, but once I press Texas the website just buffers and never loads. Can you please make sure the school is on the Scholastic list, it's name is William B Travis Elementary and the address is 300 W Carolanne Blvd, Marshall, TX 75672
IT is user friendly. as long as you have the teachers code.

I was told by one of your representatives that I can order book order flyers at the site. You have to scroll down to the bottom and order the ones you want. I couldn't locate this. I would like to have April Kindergarteners, April Seesaw and April Firefly. Thank you.
It wouldn't let me redeem my March coupon.  I had trouble submitting the order
It would be nice to have all books categorized like in a library to search.
my kids love the books..
It’s not mobile phone friendly

It is too difficult to find my kids' e-wallets from the website. Also, one of my kids has a balance on an e-gift card that I can't transfer. Why do I have to create a new e-wallet each time? I'd like to be able to find my kids and fund their accounts without having to start over each time.

Why can't I add the gift card to my cart. It takes me to another screen and ihave to add a bunch of payment stuff. It would be nice if it was all in the same system. I am super happy you added and I will eventually use but only had 30 minutes to get in and out.
Can't find the books in the flyer.  Not seeing an item number.  Bouncing between store, book club, find school page, etc.
The books are too expensive
My sons teacher states she has shared her wishlist with the families but it’s not showing on her home page
When you are selling sets of books, it would be helpful if you could list all the titles in the set.
Prices are high for my families....inner city /post covid stresses regarding poverty threshold

I couldn’t find any books on Easter that were about God. Everything is about bunnies, which is cute, but there isn’t a very big or diverse selection. I’ve been to book fairs numerous times and I’m repeatedly disappointed with the types of books offered. Some were definitely not appropriate for kids even as thrillers containing things with girls that burst into flames when upset and learning to become witches, etc. The selection offered is honest terrible. I’ve shared this with several others and they were disappointed as well. We likely won’t be purchasing much more in the future.

I noticed I get more selection when I search the whole site when I go under account and child's school I get a narrower selection - the main site sometimes can be a little cheaper. I order through school because it's a waste of money to pay for shipping even if the book is cheaper or sometimes its not on the class list (like the pokemon how to draw) I just won't order on main site since shipping is not worth the price. I may even spend more if able to select more than just flyers.
No problem
I would like to see more teaching books for me personally. Books about weather, seasons, holiday's, etc.

I put 2 books in my shopping cart earlier. I am shopping as a parent. I return to check a submitted order and logged in and went to the shop as a parent link. The 2 books I earlier put into my shopping cart are no longer in the cart. Charlotte's Web I was able to relocate and put into my cart, but Lois Lowry's Number the Stars I am unable to find under the author's name nor the book title.
I forgot to enter the birthday book coupons but a very helpful employee helped me through a chat!!
It does not say any games
I was having a hard submitting my order but I used the chat and Meagan helped me out

I mailed two checks back in august. Scholastic deposited them, but did not credit my account. I have tried dealing with it several times and I still have an account balance. I have had to bother parents to give me their banking information. It is really frustrating that an error on your side has caused more work for me and I've had to bother my parents. This does not make me want to use Scholastic going forward.
I would like to purchase a book title that is part of a pack separately, however only one of the two is available as a single and she already has that one. Other than that, all the rest was fun.
I love this site like 100/10
Awesome and easy to use! Thank you so much!
Wish you would have a section to easily find the Step in Reading books by level

I was notified that a family ordered books online. My order due date was March 24th, but when I go to submit the order it os no longer there. This is very frustrating. I don't even know which family submitted the order. I do hope they are being refunded if they paid already. Why do you have orders that expire after less than a month? I will seriously reconsider using scholastic in the future if I can't make order due dates that fit the needs of my class.

We wanted to change the class link 5-digit code on an existing order without having to redo a whole order but was told there was no way to do that.  The existing order was cancelled by the customer service representative and I will have to place the entire order again when it would be much easier (from the customer perspective) to update the 5-digit code to the new teacher of the class.  It would be nice if the website had functionality to change orders in order to update class links as necessary.
More complete details of books and pictures would be nice
easy seasonal search for holidays
All is good.
I've had to update my password a few times trying to get in. I'm not sure what I'm doing wrong.
when i went back instead of closing out I lost the page i was on but not a big deal
Wrong book from cart would move to wishlist or be removed from cart
User-friendly website!
It would be great if finding the $1 books were easier on the site.
PayPal didn’t work at first

this is just my opinion, it is really not user friendly when it comes to finding books.
Couldn’t put the class code in which is TM2KC
You charge high shipping costs to have books sent to your home. Your explanation was bogus, you are a huge company that could cut some slack to grandparents or caregivers trying to encourage reading.
I like that our class gets book benefits from us buying through here vs a store or amazon
Why is so difficult to enter coupons/free books? I haven't been able to take advantage of my "earnings" because I can't figure out how to do so!
Would love an easier way to track and earn points.  Also, to stay competitive, you should offer used books.
It was not completely easy to figure out how to find a free book
It’s not very user friendly on a cell phone
I'm finding it difficult to find my e-wallet.  I just wanted to verify the amount and can't find how to get back to it.  I did see an email, just wanted to see it on the site.
This site is unnecessarily cumbersome and buggy. Every time I try to order, it takes so long to navigate. Most of the time, I give up and just order via Amazon.
Don't feel the quality of books is as good as they used to be.
narrowing down search for classroom packs
Would love to have more nonfiction classics.
How to add a teacher to completion so instead used one on file - neither of whom I know.
No comments.
Love it! Books for a great price and helps me build my classroom library!

On a mobile device, this site was hard to navigate. Nothing showed up the right size without manual modifications to the screen and picture, and it was too easy to go back an extra page in my browser.
Always easy purchase
Hard to browse books, not user friendly

Not sure if y'all recently updated this site, but it was more challenging to navigate and actually find the books this time. Not user friendly and I cut my order short because I didn't want to deal with it anymore.
I think its a great website and I enjoy buying books for my grandchild!
I haven't received Maren's order,
The site was difficult to use.  I will have to try again tomorrow.

After placing two orders in the recently. I was notified that my daughter would receive a poster of Peppa the pig... she was excited to say the least and we weren't given any dimensions for the poster so i was basing it off the money spent $200+ so 24"x 36" for the poster to be. well the package showed up in mail today and the envelope was 12 x 18. I wanted to see my daughter's face when she pulled it out. So, all I did was cut the top open with letter opener Ever so slightly, so she can open it up. And she pulled out a piece of cardboard. Nothing else! The look in my daughter's eyes of defeat and sadness. Your company hurt my  Child not physically but Mentally and I can guarantee you that I will be informing the school About this situation and that we will no longer be participating in scholastics of any sort.  Especially after spending that amount of money for her happiness to be ripped away And believe me, it wasn't by choice. wallet doesn't work in book clubs for the schools.
moving from one page to an
We always love to look at the $2 and $3 book specials
Good site for a child’s books to keep
N/A
Site is easy to use and navigate!

Scholastic has been a wonderful tool for getting my students to read, although, I have seen a drop in interest from most middle school and high school students purchasing from the flyers and website this school year. Maybe it's because of inflation on a national level, or as some students have mentioned, it's simply because they just don't see anything they like to read on the flyers. I wish the YA flyers were still available!! And, how can I get Scholastic coupons for my students who tend to buy books regularly? I can recall a few years ago receiving a booklet of coupons from Scholastic for my students that I did not have to pay for separately!

I know things got rough for you guys during the first year or so of Covid, but I'm happy to see that Scholastic Book Clubs is back on their game! It's easy to order, things are shipped and received in a timely manner, and your rewards (coupons, etc.) are wonderful. I had to stop ordering last school year because it just wasn't worth waiting so long for a box.     Just thought you'd like to hear you're doing a great job!!!
When I try to enter a direct item number from the flyer, it always says it’s invalid.
Unable to use ewallet funds like we were told we could.
easy site to use

I wonder why I do not automatically receive your flyers AS I ALWAYS HAVE...until this year.  The only time I receive them now is if I do this online submission or talking to customer service to get them.  What changed?  I DO want the flyers each month...always have...always will!    Thanks for making this happen!!!
Was looking for book that are on the Teacher Store site...
My love of reading is shared by my granddaughters.  We spend time quietly reading and it is precious to me.
Always a pleasure!
Missing my second set of interlocking book bins

I LIKED SCHOLASTIC BETTER IN THE OLD DAYS WHEN EACH CHILD GOT 1 OR 2 FLYERS, NOT 5-10.  IT IS TOO OVERWHELMING AND PARENTS DON'T HAVE TIME TO GO THROUGH ALL OF THEM.      I ALSO LIKED THE DAYS WHEN EACH FLYER CONTAINED AT LEAST ONE GOOD HARD BACK BOOK LIKE A CLASSIC.  I.E. SHEL SILVERSTINE OR JAN BRETT

wondering if i submitted my last order

Another teacher in our District is having the same problem.  I logged on today to try to confirm through my account that indeed the order was delivered, without success.
It’s ok
Everything is geared to elementary. I teach 8th grade. Sets are geared to younger grades. The choice of books is limited and expensive for middle school.
Have an order planned, just checking with grandparents if they wish to join in on this order
Please offer Apple pay for payment
thank you for the updates to the system and for the work to get the books to us faster this year. it's much appreciated.
We LOVE TO READ!!! Would love opportunity to get some freebies or deal on books because of how often  we buy them :-)

I wish the weekly scholastic books were more aligned by grade level. They say they are 2nd grade books on the flyers but the reading levels of most of the books are around 3rd and 4th grade leveled books.   Overall, I love scholastic & I love ordering books for my classroom library. The students love seeing new books added to the shelves throughout the school year.
I had wonderful help from heather who was able to assist me in updating my account information.
I love the variety of 5 for $5 books I saw today.
Please add point values from the AR books.  It is helpful.
Great and easy site.
Wish there were more options for books about horses. Some of the books we bought in the past were not very kid friendly.
Yes. One of the students ordered an item that was listed - the order form stated that it is ONLINE - FEBRUARY.  Totally confused.
Maybe I am missing an option somewhere, but the site is not very mobile friendly.
im mad
I can't find how to set up a link for parents to buy books this month. User error I'm sure.
Better experience than the first time.
